goals.question: What is the average obesity rate across all states?
goals.visualization: bar chart of average obesity rate per state
goals.rationale: This visualization will give an overview of the obesity rate across all states and help identify states with higher or lower rates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?
goals.visualization: histogram of obesity rates per state
goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify the range of obesity rates across all states and the frequency of occurrence of each rate.

goals.question: Which state has the highest obesity rate?
goals.visualization: map of obesity rates per state
goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify the state with the highest obesity rate and its location on the map.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between obesity rate and state population?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of obesity rate vs state population
goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify if there is a correlation between obesity rate and state population and if there are any outliers.

goals.question: What is the trend of obesity rate over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of obesity rate over time
goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify if there is a trend of increasing or decreasing obesity rate over time and if there are any seasonal patterns.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data, ci=None)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average obesity rate across all states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', bins=20)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Obesity Rate')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of obesity rate over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
